  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Drought Response 2017 (PACIDA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention focus is to improve access to basic HH and food items for food security outcomes of 600 households in North Horr Sub-county through provision of cash grant. The aim is to provide purchasing power for affected households to access food and other life-saving supplies and support from local markets.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This intervention of cash transfers provides the communities with choices and opportunities.
 There is the   flexibility of purchasing food items of preference which instils dignity to affected communities. 
Accessibility to food will improve the nutritional status in the affected households, and improve food security status.
 Cash transfers avail variety of options in allocating the grant to savings that could be used to restart their livelihoods (e.g. purchase of small stock), this will avert choice of negative coping strategies, household savings will sustain them through the crisis phase enabling affected households to recover and build back their livelihood</narrative>
  </description>
